The paper discusses vulnerabilities in smart contracts, which are programs that run on blockchain platforms. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE), as well as distributed computing (cs.DC) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper analyzes data from multiple academic projects, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
